byline.original: By AMY CHOZICK, ALEXANDER BURNS and JONATHAN MARTIN

abstract: Anxiety is spreading among Democrats that Hillary Clinton has not developed effective strategy for combating unpredictable opponent Donald Trump in general election; Clinton may need to adopt far more agile and combative approach toward candidate seemingly immune to standard campaign attack strategies.
lead_paragraph: Anxiety is spreading among Democrats that Mrs. Clinton has yet to find her footing, and that her campaign is still unsure how to combat Donald Trump.

headline.main: Hillary Clinton Struggles to Find Footing in Unusual Race
headline.print_headline: Unusual Race Tests Playbook for Clinton Bid

snippet: Anxiety is spreading among Democrats that Mrs. Clinton has yet to find her footing, and that her campaign is still unsure how to combat Donald Trump.
